h=500><p><b>Druids have a use on raids.</b> <font size=2>(Score: 0)<br>by Anonymous on Saturday, March 10 @ 06:06:37 EST</font></td></tr><tr><td>Death touch fodder.</td></tr></table><br><p>[ No Comments Allowed for Anonymous, please <a href="user.php">register</a>  | <a href="comments.php?sid=135&pid=0&mode=thread&order=0&thold=0">Parent</a> ]</font><p></ul></p><a name="1051"></a><table width=99% border=0><tr bgcolor="#efefef"><td width=500><p><b>Druids are usefull</b> <font size=2>(Score: 1)<br>by Siladil on Saturday, March 10 @ 11:53:32 EST<br>(<a href="user.php?op=userinfo&uname=Siladil">User Info</a>) </font></td></tr><tr><td>My guild has 10 actively playing druids over level 50.  If you are thinking that druids are not useful on raids, then widen your thinking.  I am not going to tell you how to employ your druids, but I will give you some examples of what I mean by widening your thinking.<br>
<br>
People get entirely too hung up on having the 'perfect' mix.  These are groups that I have personally participated in.<br>
<br>
In karnors, 2 bards, shaman, druid, enchanter....did a root and dot group, no melee...worked great<br>
<br>
In chardok, cleric, enchanter, bard, shaman, enchanter, wizard.  A dot/root/charm group, worked awesome.<br>
<br>
In sebilis, paladin, druid (level 51 before the heal change), wizard, mage, sk.  Did the iksar necro area and highest person here was level 54.<br>
<br>
My point is that there are almost always more than 1 way to do things.  Don't think that just because you can't do what you have always done that your class or group is suddenly screwed.<br>
<br>
And, about the gating mobs...it is a matter of technique.  Think about what you can do to interrupt spell casting (even on mobs that are not stunable) and try that.  My guild does plane of growth every friday night (4 breast plates last night too!).  This routinely has us dealing with mobs that can't be stunned, and will gate.  There are methods of fighting to lessen the chance of this happening.  Experiment a bit, and be creative.<br>
<br>
<br>
Siladil</td></tr></table><br><p>[ No Comments Allowed for Anonymous, please <a href="user.php">register</a>  | <a href="comments.php?sid=135&pid=0&mode=thread&order=0&thold=0">Parent</a> ]</font><p><ul><li><a href="comments.php?op=showreply&tid=1057&sid=135&pid=1051&mode=thread&order=0&thold=0#1057">Re: Druids are usefull</a> by Anonymous <font size=2>on Saturday, March 10 @ 14:34:36 EST</font><br></ul></p><a name="1068"></a><table width=99% border=0><tr bgcolor="#efefef"><td width=500><p><b>Re: Dumb</b> <font size=2>(Score: 1)<br>by Smarmy on Sunday, March 11 @ 04:13:37 EST<br>(<a href="user.php?op=userinfo&uname=Smarmy">User Info</a>) </font></td></tr><tr><td>Ubermobs have uninterruptable gate spells for a specific reason (ie: to make it reasonably impossible to "pull" them to a safer location). <br>
<br>
While Verant's thinking, and the way it's applied may or may not be the best way to avoid this, having druids be able to interrupt the gate spell would more or less trivialize a lot of encounters. The queen in Chardok, for example, is difficult mostly because her personal guards respawn so fast, and she has to be fought in her throne room or she'll gate.</td></tr></table><br><p>[ No Comments Allowed for Anonymous, please <a href="user.php">register</a>  | <a href="comments.php?sid=135&pid=0&mode=thread&order=0&thold=0">Parent</a> ]</font><p><ul><li><a href="comments.php?op=showreply&tid=1110&sid=135&pid=1068&mode=thread&order=0&thold=0#1110">Re: Dumb</a> by Anonymous <font size=2>on Tuesday, March 13 @ 17:43:53 EST</font><br></ul></p></td><td bgcolor=ffffff><img src=themes/NukeNews/pixel.gif width=10 height=1 border=0></td></tr></table>

